{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S7BGanQrRY5nMtELwhfjEs","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Curation protocol — build an input pack from the raw report\n2\t\n3\tYou are a CURATOR, not a modeler. In `source/report_full_text.txt` is the full text of a\n4\ttest-facility report. Your job: extract a self-contained input pack (`pack_v2/`) that a modeling\n5\tengineer could use to PREDICT the facility's behavior — without revealing any measured outcome.\n6\t\n7\t## Extract (design/description material ONLY):\n8\t- Facility geometry & scaling (report §1.4, §3): dimensions, counts, materials, configuration.\n9\t- Instrumentation locations (§4.2): where quantities are measured (locations/types only).\n10\t- Heater system & test-case definitions (§4.3, §6.4, §7 run definitions): powers, profiles,\n11\t  configurations, ambient conditions — the CONTROLLED inputs of the baseline test (~82 kWe,\n12\t  linear profile, natural circulation, dual chimney) and the accident decay-heat scenario.\n13\t- Material properties stated in the report (emissivities, insulation conductivities).\n14\t\n15\t## STRICTLY FORBIDDEN in the pack — measured OUTCOMES, including:\n16\tany measured mass flow rate, any measured gas/wall/plate temperature from testing, measured\n17\tpressure drops, thermal efficiency or thermal (removed) power values, radiative/convective flux\n18\tmeasurements, any number from results Tables 29–51 or results §5–§7 outcome text, and any\n19\tRELAP5/CFD model result. Design-basis values (e.g. scaled duty targets in §1.4 Table 5) are\n20\tallowed — they are inputs, not measurements.\n21\t\n22\t## Output format\n23\tWrite pack_v2/01_geometry.md, 02_materials.md, 03_instrumentation.md, 04_conditions.md in your\n24\town words with all numeric values you extracted, each traceable (note the report section it came\n25\tfrom). Completeness matters: a modeler must be able to compute flow areas, heights, emissivities,\n26\theat input. When done, write pack_v2/CURATION_STATEMENT.md declaring you included no measured\n27\toutcomes.\n28\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"47d9ec1e-27f2-4086-90f4-79a8199340a9","uuid":"d00c2fad-d0c6-4f16-85aa-2970d9b79358","timestamp":"2026-07-02T09:32:42.900Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/root/curator/CURATOR_TASK.md","content":"# Curation protocol — build an input pack from the raw report\n\nYou are a CURATOR, not a modeler. In `source/report_full_text.txt` is the full text of a\ntest-facility report. Your job: extract a self-contained input pack (`pack_v2/`) that a modeling\nengineer could use to PREDICT the facility's behavior — without revealing any measured outcome.\n\n## Extract (design/description material ONLY):\n- Facility geometry & scaling (report §1.4, §3): dimensions, counts, materials, configuration.\n- Instrumentation locations (§4.2): where quantities are measured (locations/types only).\n- Heater system & test-case definitions (§4.3, §6.4, §7 run definitions): powers, profiles,\n  configurations, ambient conditions — the CONTROLLED inputs of the baseline test (~82 kWe,\n  linear profile, natural circulation, dual chimney) and the accident decay-heat scenario.\n- Material properties stated in the report (emissivities, insulation conductivities).\n\n## STRICTLY FORBIDDEN in the pack — measured OUTCOMES, including:\nany measured mass flow rate, any measured gas/wall/plate temperature from testing, measured\npressure drops, thermal efficiency or thermal (removed) power values, radiative/convective flux\nmeasurements, any number from results Tables 29–51 or results §5–§7 outcome text, and any\nRELAP5/CFD model result. Design-basis values (e.g. scaled duty targets in §1.4 Table 5) are\nallowed — they are inputs, not measurements.\n\n## Output format\nWrite pack_v2/01_geometry.md, 02_materials.md, 03_instrumentation.md, 04_conditions.md in your\nown words with all numeric values you extracted, each traceable (note the report section it came\nfrom). Completeness matters: a modeler must be able to compute flow areas, heights, emissivities,\nheat input. When done, write pack_v2/CURATION_STATEMENT.md declaring you included no measured\noutcomes.\n","numLines":28,"startLine":1,"totalLines":28}}}
