djacent chimney roles        1,500         Linear           Adjacent          Natural     Trending\n4225\t             DataQuality017 06/25/15-06/27/15      58h38m    Adjacent chimney              1,500         Linear           Adjacent          Natural     Accepted\n4226\t             DataQuality018 08/13/15-08/18/15     129h55m    GA-MHTGR accident            variable       Linear         Dual vertical       Natural     Accepted\n4227\t             DataQuality019      8/25/2015         9h08m     Baseline (repeat)             1,500         Linear         Dual vertical       Natural       Failed\n4228\t             DataQuality020 09/05/15-09/07/15      52h8m     Baseline                      1,500         Linear         Dual vertical       Natural     Accepted\n4229\t             DataQuality021   10/07/15-10/10/15    56h21m    I-NERI Test Series            1,000         Linear          Loft blowers       Forced      Trending\n4230\t\n4231\t\n4232\t\n4233\t\n4234\t                                                                                                                                                                                                                         August 2016\n4235\t             DataQuality022 01/17/16-01/22/16      120h8m    Bottom cosine                 1,500        Cosine          Dual vertical       Natural     Accepted\n4236\t             DataQuality023 02/15/16-02/23/16     190h20m    INERI test series             1,000         Linear       Reduced discharge     Forced      Accepted\n4237\t             DataQuality024 04/08/16-04/14/16     145h50m    Single chimney                1,500         Linear       Dual / Single vert.   Natural     Accepted\n4238\t             DataQuality025      5/11/2015         9h8m      Heavy-gas (argon) ingress      700          Linear         Single vertical     Natural       Failed\n4239\t             DataQuality026 05/16/16-05/20/16      97h38m    Azimuthal                     1,500     Linear / Azim.     Dual vertical       Natural     Accepted\n4240\t             DataQuality027 06/13/16-06/14/16      30h07m    Heavy gas (argon) ingress      700          Linear         Single vertical     Natural     Accepted\n4241\t\f                                                                                                                                                                        Final Project Report on RCCS Testing with the Air-Based NSTF\n4242\t                                       Table 28: Summary of air-based testing - Separate Effects & Scoping runs\n4243\t             Test Name          Date            Duration   Purpose                         Power      Heated Profile      Flow Path        Mode           Type\n4244\t\n4245\t             BakeOut001        9/4/2013          12h40m    Heater & insulation bake out       -             -                  -              -         Bakeout\n4246\t             BakeOut002        9/9/2013          05h25m    Heater & insulation bake out       -             -                  -              -         Bakeout\n4247\t             Scoping001       9/23/2013          09h20m    New instrumentation shakedown      -             -                  -              -          Scoping\n4248\t             Scoping003   02/09/15- 02/12/15     87h51m    Scoping for forced flow            -             -                  -           Forced        Scoping\n4249\t             Scoping005   06/15/15- 06/17/15     46h30m    Scoping for flexible duct          -          Linear            Adjacent        Natural       Scoping\n4250\t             SPEF001      07/27/15- 07/30/15     71h21m    Chimney break                    1,500        Linear            Adjacent        Natural   Separate Effects\n4251\t             SPEF002          10/12/2015         171h6m    Multi-parameter power/flow      variable      Linear          Loft blowers      Forced    Separate Effects\n4252\t             SPEF003      10/27-15 - 10/29/15    54h3m     Wind study / baseline            1,500        Linear          Dual vertical     Natural   Separate Effects\n4253\t             SPEF004      01/09/16- 01/15/16     54h3m     Chimney cap scoping               700         Linear          Dual vertical     Natural   Separate Effects\n4254\t             SPEF005      01/29/16- 02/08/16    232h58m    Zero power flow study              -            n/a           Dual vertical     Natural   Separate Effects\n4255\t\n4256\t\n4257\t\n4258\t\n4259\t                                                                                                                                                                        August 2016\n4260\t             SPEF006      03/01/16- 03/09/16    197h28m    Zero power flow study              -            n/a           Dual vertical     Natural   Separate Effects\n4261\t             SPEF007      04/22/16- 04/25/16     79h56m    Zero power flow study              -            n/a           Dual vertical     Natural   Separate Effects\n4262\t             SPEF008          6/27/2016          4h08m     Isothermal characterization        -            n/a         Reduced discharge   Forced    Separate Effects\n4263\t\n4264\t165\n4265\t\n4266\t\n4267\t\n4268\t\n4269\tANL-ART-47\n4270\t\f                                    Final Project Report on RCCS Testing with the Air-Based NSTF\n4271\t                                                                                      August 2016\n4272\t\n4273\t\n4274\t\n4275\t7.1     Baseline Test Cases\n4276\tA baseline test case was established to serve as a common reference for parametric studies\n4277\tand also to monitor system repeatability. These conditions simulated the depressurized\n4278\tconduction cooldown (DCC) accident scenario decay heat load of the GA-MTHGR, which\n4279\tdefined a peak power removal by the RCCS of 1.5 MWt . When scaled using similarity\n4280\tparameters derived in earlier sections, the resulting heat load on the NSTF is 56 kWt . Thus,\n4281\tour baseline test case began with a power ramp to 56 kWe , then a 2nd ramp to a higher power\n4282\tthat, with heat losses considered, would result in nominally 56 kWt within the heated test\n4283\tsection. The operating state for the test, hereby referred to as ‘baseline’ conditions, defines\n4284\tthe configuration of facility in terms of a select number of user-adjustable components:\n4285\t\n4286\t  1. Heated - riser spacing: 70.66-cm\n4287\t  2. Outlet plenum floor height: 40.64-cm\n4288\t  3. Heater profile and heat flux: Variable burst, linear 40 zones, 56 & 82 kWe\n4289\t  4. Chimney: Open vertical stacks, closed XC and fan lofts\n4290\t\n4291\t   The operating window for active test operations (powered heaters) during Run011 began\n4292\tat 10h20 on January 28th 2015 and spanned a period of 52 hours and 46 minutes. Two steady\n4293\tstate periods were maintained, the first at 56 kWe for 6 hours and the second at 82 kWe for\n4294\t16 hours. With completion of post-test data verification procedures and review of generated\n4295\tdata sets, the test was found to be fully within the defined scope and set of procedures and\n4296\tthus is classified as successful and will be submitted for qualification for Type-A data.\n4297\t   All instruments were verified and checked for working operation prior to initiating active\n4298\theating and test operations. Of the instruments included in the test documentation, none\n4299\twere found to be inoperable or out of conformance. A zero-flow condition was created by\n4300\tclosing off all five chimney valves along with sealing the inlet plenum. All signals from flow\n4301\tdevices were within expected ranges, and temperature gradients across the test structural\n4302\twere non-significant, Table 29. During the full test duration, the weather remained fair and\n4303\t\n4304\tANL-ART-47                                   166\n4305\t\fFinal Project Report on RCCS Testing with the Air-Based NSTF\n4306\tAugust 2016\n4307\t\n4308\t\n4309\ttypical for a Midwestern winter day. An overview of the weather conditions across the span\n4310\tof the testing period is given below in Table 30.\n4311\t\n4312\t                 Table 29: Pre-test zero flow system parameters for Run011\n4313\t        Zero flow values            Surface temperatures              Gas temperatures\n4314\t  Flow meter: 1.06 kg/min    Heated plate - 18.84 ◦ C    Riser inlet - 18.39 ◦ C\n4315\t  Humidity: 23.76 %          Riser duct wall - 19.81 ◦ C Riser outlet - 18.86 ◦ C\n4316\t  Riser ∆P 1 − 12 : +0.93P a Adia. west wall - 19.48 ◦ C Chimney inlet - 20.72 ◦ C\n4317\t  Chimney ∆P N, S : +0.03P a Ceramic heaters - 18.45 ◦ C Chimney outlet - 20.27 ◦ C\n4318\t\n4319\t\n4320\t\n4321\t\n4322\t        Table 30: Summary of weather conditions during full test window of Run011\n4323\t                                          Average         Span\n4324\t                Rain (total)                 0.0       0.0 - 0.25         mm\n4325\t                Rate fall rate               0          0.0 - 0.0       mm/hr\n4326\t                Barometric pressure        765.53     754.8 - 776.7       mm\n4327\t\n4328\t                                                                            ◦\n4329\t                Indoor temperature          23.14      21.9 - 24.7              C\n4330\t                                                                            ◦\n4331\t                Outdoor temperature         -0.12       - 6 - 2.8               C\n4332\t\n4333\t                Indoor humidity             21.14      16.0 - 26.0           %\n4334\t                Outdoor humidity            68.87      46.0 - 86.0           %\n4335\t\n4336\t                Wind run                    0.24        0 - 0.59           km\n4337\t                                                                                ◦\n4338\t                Wind direction             244.17     22.5 - 337.5\n4339\t                Wind direction              NW        NNE - NNW       direction\n4340\t                Wind speed                  4.02         0 - 9.8           m/s\n4341\t\n4342\t\n4343\t\n4344\t7.1.1     General System Behavior at Baseline Conditions\n4345\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"47d9ec1e-27f2-4086-90f4-79a8199340a9","uuid":"9dce888c-71e5-4304-b8bf-007591a7e177","timestamp":"2026-07-02T09:34:57.666Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/root/curator/source/report_full_text.txt","content":"Chapter 7\n\nTesting Results\nThe following chapter details the tests completed within the air-based NSTF program at\nArgonne. Spanning a 33-month period, a total of 2,250 hours of active test operations were\nconducted. A high-level summary of each test’s purpose, date completed, varied parameter,\nand classification is first provided by Tables 27 and 28. Following, a detailed discussion\nincluding testing conditions, facility configuration, and results will be provided on selected\ntests of primary interest.\n\n\n\n\n                                               163                                ANL-ART-47\n\fANL-ART-47\n                                             Table 27: Summary of air-based testing - Data Quality runs\n             Test Name              Date          Duration   Purpose                      Power,        Profile          Flow Path          Mode      Classification\n\n             DataQuality001   02/12/14-02/13/14    28h10m    Baseline                      1,500         Linear         Dual vertical       Natural       Failed\n             DataQuality002   02/24/14-02/26/14    49h46m    Baseline                      1,500         Linear         Dual vertical       Natural     Trending\n             DataQuality003   03/10/14-03/12/14    50h02m    Baseline                      1,500         Linear         Dual vertical       Natural     Trending\n             DataQuality004 04/09/14-04/11/14      49h52m    Baseline                      1,500         Linear         Dual