, kWt) measurements.\n- No measured radiative/convective heat-flux values.\n- No values from results Tables 29–51 (e.g. Tables 29, 30, 32, 34–40, 43–45, 50, 51), nor from\n  results narrative in §5 and §7 outcome text.\n- No RELAP5-3D or STAR-CCM+/CFD model results (including CFD-derived view factors from §6.4.3).\n\n## Judgment calls (allowed inputs that could be mistaken for outcomes)\n- **Table 5 / Table 25 scaled duty targets** (decay power, heat flux, ΔT, system flow) are included:\n  the task explicitly permits these as design-basis *inputs*, not measurements.\n- **Heated-plate emissivity 0.78–0.79** (§3.3.3) is included as a pre-test *material/surface property*\n  (a radiation modeling input), not a facility-performance result.\n- **Heat-flux-sensor Kradiative sensitivities** (Table 13) are included as per-sensor *calibration\n  constants* accompanying the location list, not as measured fluxes.\n- **Reference air/argon physical properties** (Tables 46, 47) are included as standard *published\n  fluid properties* (working-fluid inputs), not facility measurements — flagged as such in the file.\n- **Ambient/meteorological conditions** (outdoor temperature envelope −18.1 to +32.1 °C from §1.5;\n  seasonal averages for the accident runs from §7.3.2 prose) are included as external *boundary-\n  condition inputs*. These were taken from narrative text, not from the forbidden weather results\n  tables (Tables 30, 36). Specific per-run measured weather from those tables was not copied.\n\nAll numeric values carry a source section/table reference for traceability.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01Dy76wkjJwkHmQoPAHqTsM4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The curation is complete. I built the input pack in `pack_v2/` by working through the report section by section (read in chunks), extracting only design/description/controlled-input material and excluding every measured outcome.\n\n## What I produced\n\n**`01_geometry.md`** — Scaling basis (1/2 axial scale, lR=0.5; Tables 3–5), GA-MHTGR reference (Table 2), and full as-built geometry from §3: base/framework, inlet downcomer (24″, 184.5″ eq. length), inlet plenum (volumes, port dims), 12 riser ducts (10″×2″×0.188″, lengths), outlet plenum, dual chimney (Table 8 segment lengths), blowers, heated cavity (22 ft × 52″, adjustable depth), heater sub-panels, adjustable-features table, and full-scale loop elevations/ratios (Tables 56, 57). Enough to compute flow areas, heights, and volumes.\n\n**`02_materials.md`** — Steel/aluminum grades, heated-plate composition, all emissivities (plate 0.78–0.79, sub-panel 0.90, sensor surfaces, cavity sidewall 0.2), insulation Table 9 conductivities, and reference air/argon fluid properties (Tables 46–47).\n\n**`03_instrumentation.md`** — DAQ hardware, the Table 12 sensor inventory (types/ranges/accuracy), and measurement *locations only* for wall TCs, the 19 heat-flux sensors (duct/side/elevation), meteorological, ΔP, inlet flow, hot-wire, pitot, gas-temperature rakes, and Luna fibers (ducts #6/#9).\n\n**`04_conditions.md`** — Heater system (220 kWe, 40 zones, 80/20 main/guard), the baseline definition (~82 kWe, linear, natural circulation, dual vertical chimney), the accident decay-heat scenario (Table 25 scaling + the full programmed power polynomial with Pscale=90), cosine (Table 26) and azimuthal (125/75) profiles, off-normal run definitions, and the ambient boundary envelope.\n\n**`CURATION_STATEMENT.md`** — Declares no measured outcomes and documents the judgment calls (Table 5/25 duty targets, plate emissivity, sensor calibration constants, reference fluid properties, and ambient boundary conditions — all inputs, not facility responses).\n\n## Key exclusions honored\nNo measured flows, gas/wall/plate/heater temperatures, pressure drops, thermal power/efficiency, or heat fluxes; nothing from results Tables 29–51 or §5/§7 outcome text; no RELAP5/CFD results (including the CFD-derived view factors in §6.4.3 — I kept only the resulting 125/75 controlled power split). A grep check across the pack surfaced only legitimate material specs and reference properties, no leaked results."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1593,"cache_read_input_tokens":153107,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1593},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"47d9ec1e-27f2-4086-90f4-79a8199340a9","uuid":"640c9d7d-b39a-4456-9cc0-ba888458cde3","request_id":"req_011Ccd1eSCh1uom2jHvK1aid"}
